<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-26T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.60C 3/214: Telegram (part
                                air)</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cudahy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-27T00:00:00+01:00">December 27, 1934—12
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 29—7:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>59. Your instruction No. 138, December 12, page 4 second
                                    paragraph.<note n="41" xml:id="d522fn41">Paragraph beginning,
                                    “In view of the extraterritorial status …”, above.</note> What
                                is the status of American employees of the Embassy <pb facs="0737" n="661" xml:id="pg_661"/> other than officers with respect to
                                liability to contribute portion cost of insurance of Polish
                                nationals personally employed by them?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cudahy</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>